page.title: 18Sheila Baker's Day.
page.content: Mrs Sheila Baker gets up at 7am and makes a drink.After her drink she feeds her cats and takes her son to school.She also lets her dogs out.But she has no breakfast. She goes to work at 9am and if there are no customers she tidies the shelves.She has a cup of tea at 9am and 11-30am.At 1pm she goes home.When she is home she prepares her vegetables. She feeds her cats and lets her dogs out.She makes a snack.At 2-15pm she goes to work.At 5pm she leaves the mini shop. In the evening she washes up and prepares sandwiches for the next day.She goes to bed at 10pm.
